    <h2>1. Artificial Intelligence (AI) APIs</h2>
    <p>The AI revolution continues to expand, and accessing powerful models has never been easier. Here are the top free AI APIs.</p>

    <h3>1.1 OpenAI (Free Tier / Trial)</h3>
    <p>OpenAI provides access to state-of-the-art language models like GPT-4o-mini and various embedding models. While primarily a paid service, new users often receive free credits, and the usage costs for smaller models are incredibly low, making it effectively free for small-scale development.</p>
    <p><strong>Key features:</strong> Text generation, image generation (DALL-E), text-to-speech, and transcription.</p>

    <h3>1.2 Hugging Face Inference API</h3>
    <p>Hugging Face hosts thousands of open-source machine learning models. Their Inference API allows you to run models for natural language processing, computer vision, and audio tasks directly without managing infrastructure.</p>
    <p><strong>Key features:</strong> Access to models like Llama, BERT, and Stable Diffusion. Generous free tier for prototyping.</p>

    <h3>1.3 Replicate</h3>
    <p>Replicate makes it easy to run open-source models with an API. While they operate on a pay-as-you-go model, they offer a small amount of free compute for new users to test models like Llama 3 or SDXL.</p>

    <h3>1.4 Google Gemini API</h3>
    <p>Google's Gemini API offers a generous free tier for developers to access their latest multimodal models. It is highly capable of processing text, images, and audio simultaneously.</p>

    <p><em>Read our full guide on <a href="/free-ai-apis">Free AI APIs</a> for more details.</em></p>

    <h2>2. Weather APIs</h2>
    <p>Weather data is one of the most common integrations for mobile apps and dashboards.</p>

    <h3>2.1 OpenWeatherMap</h3>
    <p>A staple in the developer community, OpenWeatherMap provides current weather data, minute forecasts, and historical data. The free tier allows up to 1,000 API calls per day.</p>

    <h3>2.2 Open-Meteo</h3>
    <p>Open-Meteo is an open-source weather API that requires no API key for non-commercial use. It offers high-resolution forecasts and historical weather data directly from national weather services.</p>

    <h3>2.3 Visual Crossing</h3>
    <p>Visual Crossing provides global historical weather data and forecasts. Their free tier is generous, offering 1,000 records per day, which is excellent for data analysis and machine learning projects.</p>

    <h3>2.4 WeatherAPI</h3>
    <p>Provides current weather, forecasts, and astronomy data. The free tier allows 1,000,000 calls per month, making it one of the most generous offerings available.</p>

    <p><em>Explore more in our <a href="/free-weather-apis">Free Weather APIs</a> deep dive.</em></p>

    <h2>3. Maps & Geolocation APIs</h2>
    <p>Integrating maps and location services is essential for logistics, travel, and local business applications.</p>

    <h3>3.1 Google Maps Platform</h3>
    <p>While a premium service, Google Maps offers a $200 recurring monthly credit, which covers a significant amount of usage for Maps, Routes, and Places APIs for small projects.</p>

    <h3>3.2 Mapbox</h3>
    <p>Mapbox offers highly customizable maps and navigation services. Their free tier includes 50,000 map loads per month, making it a popular alternative to Google Maps.</p>

    <h3>3.3 OpenStreetMap (OSM) via Overpass API</h3>
    <p>OpenStreetMap is a free, editable map of the world. The Overpass API allows you to query OSM data for specific features, such as finding all restaurants in a bounding box.</p>

    <h3>3.4 Leaflet</h3>
    <p>While not an API itself, Leaflet is the leading open-source JavaScript library for interactive maps. It works seamlessly with tile providers like Mapbox and OSM.</p>

    <h3>3.5 HERE Technologies</h3>
    <p>HERE provides enterprise-grade mapping APIs. Their freemium plan offers generous transaction limits for routing, geocoding, and map rendering.</p>

    <p><em>Learn how to integrate these in our <a href="/free-maps-apis">Free Maps APIs</a> guide.</em></p>

    <h2>4. Finance & Market Data APIs</h2>
    <p>Building fintech apps requires reliable data sources for stocks, currencies, and cryptocurrencies.</p>

    <h3>4.1 Alpha Vantage</h3>
    <p>Alpha Vantage provides historical and real-time stock APIs, forex, and cryptocurrency data. The free tier allows up to 500 API calls per day.</p>

    <h3>4.2 Yahoo Finance API (Unofficial)</h3>
    <p>While Yahoo deprecated its official public API, several rapidAPI wrappers and Python libraries (like yfinance) provide free access to Yahoo's comprehensive financial data.</p>

    <h3>4.3 CoinGecko</h3>
    <p>For cryptocurrency data, CoinGecko offers a completely free, public API with no keys required, providing current prices, historical data, and market volume for thousands of coins.</p>

    <h3>4.4 Polygon.io</h3>
